@format ezf/0.1
@resource Bundle : Resource
@description A container for a collection of resources.

@elements
identifier       : 0..1 Identifier        [Σ] # Persistent identifier for the bundle
type             : 1..1 code              [Σ] # document | message | transaction | transaction-response | batch | batch-respons…
  @binding required http://hl7.org/fhir/ValueSet/bundle-type
timestamp        : 0..1 instant           [Σ] # When the bundle was assembled
total            : 0..1 unsignedInt       [Σ] # If search, the total number of matches
link             : 0..* BackboneElement   [Σ] # Links related to this Bundle
  relation       : 1..1 code              [Σ] # See http://www.iana.org/assignments/link-relations/link-relations.xhtml#link-re…
    @binding required http://hl7.org/fhir/ValueSet/iana-link-relations
  url            : 1..1 uri               [Σ] # Reference details for the link
entry            : 0..* BackboneElement   [Σ] # Entry in the bundle - will have a resource or information
  link           : 0..* @ref(Bundle.link)  [Σ] # Links related to this entry
  fullUrl        : 0..1 uri               [Σ] # URI for resource (e.g. the absolute URL server address, URI for UUID/OID, etc.)
  resource       : 0..1 Resource          [Σ] # A resource in the bundle
  search         : 0..1 BackboneElement   [Σ] # Search related information
    mode         : 0..1 code              [Σ] # match | include - why this is in the result set
      @binding required http://hl7.org/fhir/ValueSet/search-entry-mode
    score        : 0..1 decimal           [Σ] # Search ranking (between 0 and 1)
  request        : 0..1 BackboneElement   [Σ] # Additional execution information (transaction/batch/history)
    method       : 1..1 code              [Σ] # GET | HEAD | POST | PUT | DELETE | PATCH
      @binding required http://hl7.org/fhir/ValueSet/http-verb
    url          : 1..1 uri               [Σ] # URL for HTTP equivalent of this entry
    ifNoneMatch  : 0..1 string            [Σ] # For managing cache validation
    ifModifiedSince : 0..1 instant           [Σ] # For managing cache currency
    ifMatch      : 0..1 string            [Σ] # For managing update contention
    ifNoneExist  : 0..1 string            [Σ] # For conditional creates
  response       : 0..1 BackboneElement   [Σ] # Results of execution (transaction/batch/history)
    status       : 1..1 string            [Σ] # Status response code (text optional)
    location     : 0..1 uri               [Σ] # The location (if the operation returns a location)
    etag         : 0..1 string            [Σ] # The Etag for the resource (if relevant)
    lastModified : 0..1 instant           [Σ] # Server's date time modified
    outcome      : 0..1 Resource          [Σ] # OperationOutcome with hints and warnings (for batch/transaction)
signature        : 0..1 Signature         [Σ] # Digital Signature
issues           : 0..1 Resource          [Σ] # Issues with the Bundle

@invariants
bdl-1    : total only when a search or history
bdl-2    : entry.search only when a search
bdl-7    : FullUrl must be unique in a bundle, or else entries with the same fullUrl must have different meta.versionId (except in history bundles)
bdl-9    : A document must have an identifier with a system and a value
bdl-10   : A document must have a date
bdl-11   : A document must have a Composition as the first resource
bdl-12   : A message must have a MessageHeader as the first resource
bdl-13   : A subscription-notification must have a SubscriptionStatus as the first resource
bdl-14   : entry.request.method PATCH not allowed for history
bdl-15   : Bundle resources where type is not transaction, transaction-response, batch, or batch-response or when the request is a POST SHALL have Bundle.entry.fullUrl populated
bdl-16   : Issue.severity for all issues within the OperationOutcome must be either 'information' or 'warning'.
bdl-17   : Use and meaning of issues for documents has not been validated because the content will not be rendered in the document.
bdl-18   : Self link is required for searchsets.
bdl-3a   : For collections of type document, message, searchset or collection, all entries must contain resources, and not have request or response elements
bdl-3b   : For collections of type history, all entries must contain request or response elements, and resources if the method is POST, PUT or PATCH
bdl-3c   : For collections of type transaction or batch, all entries must contain request elements, and resources if the method is POST, PUT or PATCH
bdl-3d   : For collections of type transaction-response or batch-response, all entries must contain response elements
bdl-5    : must be a resource unless there's a request or response
bdl-8    : fullUrl cannot be a version specific reference
